In 863 CE, "Adachi-no-Kami" was promoted to {{nihongo|Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade|従五位上|1=Junior Fifth Rank|lt=Junior Fifth Rank, Upper Grade}}, and in 865 CE, "Udachi-no-Kami" was elevated to {{nihongo|Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|従四位下|lt=Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade|1=Junior Fourth Rank}}. These honors likely refer to Morita-no-Kami.

== Genealogy ==
[[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|170px|thumb|Genealogy of the {{ill|Moriya clan|ja|守矢氏|1=Moriya clan|qq=draft}}]]

Morita-no-Kami is the son of {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Yasakatome|ja|八坂刀売神|qq=draft}}. His children include {{ill|Koshinao-no-Kami|ja|高志奈男神|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Mitutama-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|美都多麻比売命|qq=draft}}.

Mitutama-hime-no-Mikoto bore {{ill|Yakushi-no-Kami|ja|八櫛神|qq=draft}} with {{ill|Katakurabe-no-Mikoto|ja|片倉辺命|qq=draft}}. Yakushi-no-Kami is considered the fifth head of the Moriya clan.

